column5: Hit one small muskie right off the bat Sunday morning and didn't see another until almost 12 hours later when I hit this nice one.  She measured, 48" x 19" and made the mid-day lull worthwhile.  Not a great day for numbers but fortunately we made up for it with size.
Great report Doctrt  She's a real beaut  Thanks for sharing Leechman
Nice fish!
thats a nice fish Doc..... Lemme see....got the small one right off the bat in the AM. .then this one 12hrs later.......about 7,8,9pm????? Just curious......I see your boat lights on.
Definitley worth the wait!! Congrats on a beaut!! What did you take her on if you don't mind telling?  Cheers, 1leg
Thats a very healthy looking musky!Makes sense. Musky are most active either early morning or evening/night.
huge fish, thanks for the report!  cheers!
NICE Tim I cant find the time to get out dammit
Great shot.. that's a huge Muskie.. Congrats on the catch.
she's real perdy

I know Tim's" secret bait" that he's been lighting it up with this year.I will gladly sell this info as soon as I find one for myself.Tim- unreal run your on and if you can't get out this weekend could I borrow that thing?
Gorgeous Tim!  Nice to see more of your pictures this year....keep em coming!   Looks like there might be an auction for your hot lure soon  hehe
WOW...like someone else already said...well worth the wait.....that is an awesome specimen....co  ngrats.
Now that's a nice lookin girl!!....Great pic!!
Nice musky bud !!!!!   job well done...cheers
A very nice healthy uninjured muskie. A beautiful fish.
Thats a great catch, makes the slow day worthwhile.
very nice looking ski!
good job
Nice Fish!! Funny how one fish can make a good day (its always a good day when you can get out) of fishing GREAT !!  Meely
